This project incorporates or is inspired by several open-source projects and 
resources. We acknowledge and thank the following projects and their contributors:

1. HYPRLAND
   Repository: https://github.com/hyprwm/Hyprland
   License: BSD 3-Clause License
   Copyright: Hyprland Development Team
   
   This project installs and configures Hyprland, which is licensed under the
   BSD 3-Clause License. We are not affiliated with the Hyprland project.

2. DRACULA THEME
   Repository: https://github.com/dracula/dracula-theme
   License: MIT License
   Copyright: Dracula Theme Organization
   
   This project applies the Dracula color scheme across various applications.
   All Dracula theme configurations are used under the MIT License.

3. LAZYGIT
   Repository: https://github.com/jesseduffield/lazygit
   License: MIT License
   Copyright: Jesse Duffield
   
   LazyGit is installed as part of the development environment setup.

4. LAZYDOCKER
   Repository: https://github.com/jesseduffield/lazydocker
   License: MIT License
   Copyright: Jesse Duffield
   
   LazyDocker is installed as part of the development environment setup.

5. NEOVIM & LAZYVIM
   Neovim Repository: https://github.com/neovim/neovim
   LazyVim Repository: https://github.com/LazyVim/LazyVim
   License: Apache License 2.0 (Neovim), Apache License 2.0 (LazyVim)
   
   This project configures Neovim with LazyVim for the development environment.

6. ALACRITTY
   Repository: https://github.com/alacritty/alacritty
   License: Apache License 2.0
   Copyright: Alacritty Contributors
   
   Alacritty terminal emulator is configured with Dracula theme.

7. WAYBAR
   Repository: https://github.com/Alexays/Waybar
   License: MIT License
   Copyright: Alexis Rouillard
   
   Waybar is configured as the status bar for Hyprland.

8. UV (Python Package Manager)
   Repository: https://github.com/astral-sh/uv
   License: MIT License or Apache License 2.0
   Copyright: Astral Software Inc.
   
   UV is installed as the modern Python package manager.

9. OPENTOFU
   Repository: https://github.com/opentofu/opentofu
   License: Mozilla Public License 2.0
   Copyright: OpenTofu Community
   
   OpenTofu is installed as the open-source Terraform alternative.

10. DOCKER
    Website: https://www.docker.com/
    The project includes Docker-based testing but does not modify Docker itself.
    Docker usage is subject to Docker's terms of service.

11. VARIOUS LINUX DISTRIBUTIONS
    This project supports and has been tested on:
    - Ubuntu (Canonical Ltd.)
    - Debian (Debian Project)
    - Arch Linux (Arch Linux Community)
    - Fedora (Red Hat, Inc.)
    - openSUSE (SUSE LLC)
    
    All distribution-specific code respects the respective distribution's
    packaging guidelines and policies.

================================================================================

DISTRIBUTION-SPECIFIC ACKNOWLEDGMENTS

ARCH LINUX:
- Uses AUR (Arch User Repository) packages
- Incorporates yay AUR helper
- Follows Arch packaging standards

UBUNTU/DEBIAN:
- Uses official repositories and approved PPAs
- Follows Debian policy guidelines
- Respects Ubuntu's package management conventions

FEDORA:
- Uses official repositories and approved COPR repositories
- Follows Fedora packaging guidelines
- Incorporates RPM Fusion repositories where appropriate

OPENSUSE:
- Uses official repositories and Packman repository
- Follows openSUSE Build Service conventions
- Respects SUSE packaging standards

